## [conftest.py](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/tests/conftest.py) Mock Integrity

[MockAuditLedger](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/tests/conftest.py#17-49) and [MockIdentityServicePolicy](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/tests/conftest.py#57-94) both **properly inherit from their ABCs** ([AuditLedgerInterface](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/interfaces.py#13-29), [IdentityServiceInterface](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/interfaces.py#31-47)). This is correct — these are not monkey-patches or `unittest.mock.Mock()` objects. They are deterministic, in-process implementations of the kernel interfaces, appropriate for unit testing components in isolation.

> [!NOTE]
> These are **test doubles implementing ABCs**, not arbitrary mocks. They follow the same contract as production code.

---

## Conclusion

The codebase is **structurally sound and production-grade** for Phase 1 and Phase 2. All quality gates pass with zero violations. No compromised code, no silent failures, no suppressed warnings. The kernel is ready for Phase 3.
